                Vaccination Program
            </h3>
            <p>
                Puppies and kittens are due for the first vaccine shot at 6-8 weeks of age. The second vaccine shot is a month later, the third one is at 3-4 months of age. Annual vaccine is required to protect your pet from common infectious diseases e.g., Rabies, Distemper, Hepatitis, Parainfluenza, Parvo Virus, Leptospirosis, and Bordetella in dogs. Rabies, Panleukopenia, Calicivirus, Feline Rhinoracheitis, Feline Leukemia, and FIV in cats
            </p>
        </section>
